Question;Answer
When did Christianity begin?;Christianity began with the birth of Jesus Christ, over 2000 years ago.
Who is the founder of Christianity?;Jesus Christ
What are the teachings of Jesus Christ?;a)God is a Father to all people and Jesus is the savior b)People are called to love and forgive others c)People are called to ask forgiveness of sins and repent d. People are called to deny themselves and follow Jesus
Who were the leaders of the early Christian Church?;The Apostles
How did Jesus die?;Romans crucified him.
What did the Apostolic Fathers do?;They wrote about Christianity and spread the news of Jesus.
What did Romans do to Christians?;Romans persecuted Christians
What did Emperor Theodosius do in A.D. 380?;He made Catholic Christianity the official religion of the Roman Empire.
